                "content": "You are an information extraction assistant.\n\nYour task is to convert Google Meet Gemini meeting notes into structured JSON.\n\nExtract only the information that exists in the meeting notes.\n\nDo not summarize beyond what is already provided.\n\nIf a section does not exist, return an empty string or an empty array.\n\nReturn valid JSON only that matches the required schema."
              },
              {
                "content": "=Convert the following Google Meet Gemini meeting notes into structured JSON.\n\nReturn ONLY valid JSON using the following schema:\n\n{\n  \"meeting\": {\n    \"title\": \"\",\n    \"meeting_type\": \"AI & Digitalization Weekly Sync\",\n    \"date\": \"\",\n    \"quarter\": \"\",\n    \"summary\": \"\",\n    \"source_document\": \"\"\n  },\n  \"decisions\": [],\n  \"action_items\": [\n    {\n      \"owners\": [],\n      \"task\": \"\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n\nRules:\n\n1. Set meeting.title using the provided Meeting Title.\n\n2. Set meeting.date using the provided Meeting Date.\n\n3. Determine meeting.quarter from the meeting date using the following rules:\n   - January to April → Q1\n   - May to August → Q2\n   - September to December → Q3\n   Return only the quarter (for example: \"Q2\").\n\n4. Set meeting.summary using only the Summary section.\n\n5. Populate decisions with every item listed under the Decisions section.\n\n6. Populate action_items using only the Next steps section.\n\n7. Each action item begins with one or more owners enclosed in square brackets.\n\n   Example:\n   [Nyairo Kemunto] Populate prompt library\n\n   becomes\n\n   {\n     \"owners\": [\"Nyairo Kemunto\"],\n     \"task\": \"Populate prompt library\"\n   }\n\n   Example:\n\n   [Florian Döbler, Nyairo Kemunto] Project check in\n\n   becomes\n\n   {\n     \"owners\": [\n       \"Florian Döbler\",\n       \"Nyairo Kemunto\"\n     ],\n     \"task\": \"Project check in\"\n   }\n\n8. Set meeting.source_document using the Google Docs URL below, replacing {FILE_ID} with the provided File ID.\nFormat:\n\nhttps://docs.google.com/document/d/{FILE_ID}/edit\n\n9. Return valid JSON only.\n\nMeeting Title:\n{{ $json.body.meetingTitle }}\n\nMeeting Date:\n{{ $json.body.date }}\n\nMeeting Notes:\n{{ $json.body.notesContent }}\n\nFile ID:\n{{ $json.body.fileId }}"
              }
            ]
